----------------- Infrastructure As A Service --------------------

1. Databases (50GB Hard Disk)
2. EC2 Servers (8GB RAM, 2 Core CPU)
3. eg :- RDBMS, NRDBMS


-------------------- Platform As A Service ----------------------

1. Lambda Service (where u have to run your code directly and this will be all managed, scaled by AWS)
2. ECS => Elastic Container Service (create docker container and put into the ECS so it will be auto-scaled, managed by AWS).
3. EKS => Elastic Kubernetes Service (runs your kubernetes cluster in AWS managed EKS service).

So all above becomes your Platform as a Service.


----------------------- Software As A Service ------------------------

1. Gmail is Software as a Service
2. Learning Management System (LMS) plaform is also an example of Software as a Service.

Some services are provided by AWS under Software as a Service.